# Cursor agent matrix (all agents)

Thin orchestration for **every** Cursor agent. Do not re-essay sibling rules.

| Agent | Default plane | UniGrok when | Pointer |
|-------|---------------|--------------|---------|
| Composer / chat | Composer Grok 4.5 | Dual-plane cost/route, research, `@grok` peer review | `cursor-unigrok-routing.mdc` |
| Bugbot Autofix | Composer edit on given PR head | Advisory only — never a second silent rewriter | `cursor-bugbot-autofix.mdc` |
| PR Approver | Single-pass approve/comment | Optional peer review via UniGrok | `cursor-automations-single-pass.mdc` |
| Security Reviewer | Single-pass security findings | Optional peer review via UniGrok | `cursor-automations-single-pass.mdc` |
| Automations coordinator | Coordination / Ready→Live handoff to Codex | Status probes only | `cursor-automations-single-pass.mdc` |
| Cloud Agents | Fail-closed remote/API only | Never `localhost:4765` / laptop secrets | `cursor-cloud-local-boundary.mdc` |

## Shared law (all agents)

- **Identity:** local hybrid UniGrok uses `X-Client-ID: cursor` or `cursor-forge`. Bare `http:anon` is not a healthy Cursor path.
- **UniGrok modes:** `fast` = cheap checks; `reasoning` / `thinking` = hard design; `research` = external evidence; `auto` when unsure. Do not thrash modes on one finding.
- **Authorization:** sponsor standing order for Cursor-agent fixes → `cursor-agent-authorization.mdc`.
- **Handoff:** Cursor ships **Ready** packets; **Live** land = Codex / supervisor only. Do not fight peer Gemini / Copilot / Claude / Grok packets.
- **Leave alone:** `docs/ide-setup.md`, repo-root `.mcp.json`, peer brand worktrees/PRs.
- **Provable calls:** when invoking UniGrok, prefer recording `client_id` + `model` + `plane` + `cost_usd` / billing class for human radio.
